Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Cytidine 5'-Diphosphocholine Sodium in Water and Different Binary Mixtures from (278.15 to 298.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental solubility data were measured for cytidine 5'-diphosphocholine sodium dissolved in water and methanol + water, ethanol + water, and acetone + water from (278.15 to 298.15) K. All of the experiments were carried out under atmospheric pressure by an isothermal method. The solubility data were correlated by the modified Apelblat equation. Computation showed that the model fit the data well.
